# ADR-003: Parser architecture

## Context

Our PDF parser needs to cleanly extract holding data: shares and ticker symbol based on Robinhood brokerage format.

## Decision

Library: pdfplumber.
- Cleanly extracts text from Robinhood statements but realized that it doesn't detect tables.
- We tried table extraction first via extract_tables() which didnt return anything since it's just text positioned. 
- Switched to text extraction via extract_text() which gives us text  suitable for parsing.

Approach: text extraction then line-by-line parsing each token
- Same structure every holding so this makes it very easy

Function signature: def parse_robinhood_statement(file_path: str) -> list[ParsedHolding]

Failure: raised ParseError which will be a custom exception
- Catches and updates the status of the statement (Statement.status = "failed")
- Also keeping original PDF for future debugging purposes + storing error message in new column

Trigger for parser: sync inline with upload_statement endpoint
- If latency for parsing gets too long then move it to background async.

Holding update strategy: Replace it. 
- On successful parse, replace all existing previous data with the newly parsed data. Simplest way to go about it for now.
- In the future, maybe per-statement Holdings for past timeline comparisons.

## Status
Accepted
